Durban - An armed robber was shot dead during a home invasion in Weenen this week. According to police three armed men accosted a businessman and his wife at their home. It is alleged two suspects had accosted the man in his garage where they assaulted him while the third suspect entered the home and began assaulting the wife. "The suspect demanded cash and the safe key from the wife. Police received a report of the robbery and responded. The suspects spotted the police and a shoot-out ensued. "One suspect sustained a gunshot wound. He was disarmed and arrested. The second suspect cooperated with police and handed himself over while the third suspect was fatally wounded during the shootout," said police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala She said police recovered three pistols and several rounds of ammunition at the scene. A case of robbery, attempted murder as well as possession of firearms and ammunition. The two suspects aged 34 and 49 will appear in the Weenen Magistrates Court on Friday. POST